        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(policy): gate product-direction PR closes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add a distinct `unconfirmed_product_direction` review outcome for technically correct, well-proven external feature PRs without maintainer-confirmed direction\n- keep actual closure behind `CLAWSWEEPER_UNCONFIRMED_PRODUCT_DIRECTION_CLOSE_ENABLED`, defaulting to false\n- fail closed on age, inactivity, assignment, requested review, maintainer comments/reviews, protected automation labels, state drift, or GitHub fetch failures\n- keep paired issue/PR closure from bypassing the policy gate\n\n## Decision\n\nLanding this PR enables durable closure proposals and review comments. It does **not** enable automatic closure. A separate repository-variable decision is required before apply can close any matching PR.\n\nThe policy deliberately exempts `clawsweeper:human-review`, `clawsweeper:manual-only`, `clawsweeper:autofix`, and `clawsweeper:automerge`.\n\nNo merge behavior changes. Automatically generated PRs remain manual-merge only.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm run check`\n- autoreview: clean after fixing paired-close preflight\n\nCloses https://github.com/openclaw/clawsweeper/issues/218\n",
